---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | San Blas Islands"
  description="Privacy policy for San Blas Travel: what information we collect when you book a tour, and how it's used."
  path="/legal/privacy"
  availableLocales={['en', 'es']}
>
  <Breadcrumbs items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Privacy Policy' }]} />

  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 pb-16 pt-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl font-semibold text-deep sm:text-5xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-deep/50">Last updated: July 13, 2026</p>
    <p class="mt-4 rounded-xl border border-amber/40 bg-amber/10 px-4 py-3 text-sm text-deep/70">
      Initial draft — under review by the business (and a legal advisor) before being treated as final.
    </p>

    <div class="prose prose-headings:font-heading prose-headings:text-deep prose-a:text-teal mt-8 max-w-none">
      <h2>1. What information we collect</h2>
      <p>When you book a tour, we collect your name, email, WhatsApp number, and, if applicable, your pickup location (hotel or address). If you pay by card, payment processing is handled securely by our payment provider — we don't store your full card details.</p>

      <h2>2. What we use your information for</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Coordinating and confirming your booking.</li>
        <li>Sending your confirmation, reminders, and receipts by email or WhatsApp.</li>
        <li>Contacting you if there are changes to your tour (for example, due to weather).</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Who we share your information with</h2>
      <p>We don't sell your information. We share it only with providers necessary to operate your booking (payment processor, and local island guides/operators who need your name and traveler count).</p>

      <h2>4. Your rights</h2>
      <p>You can request that we correct or delete your contact information by messaging us on WhatsApp.</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
